1
00:00:00,436 --> 00:00:01,742
Previously on One Tree Hill.

2
00:00:01,772 --> 00:00:03,591
Oh, hey Mouth, have you seen Brooke?

3
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,573
Yeah, she’s um… benefiting with Felix.

4
00:00:08,809 --> 00:00:12,115
My mom ever asks… I got the test and I’m fine.

5
00:00:12,546 --> 00:00:13,524
If that’s what you want.

6
00:00:13,631 --> 00:00:17,865
Yesterday Dan… told me that you slept with Keith. Is it true?

7
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:19,443
No, of course not.

8
00:00:19,750 --> 00:00:22,915
I spent the whole night waiting for you! All while you were with Chris!

9
00:00:22,985 --> 00:00:26,421
- Can we leave him out of this please?! 
- Why? Are you into him?

10
00:00:26,646 --> 00:00:30,651
Just because people say something, doesn’t make it true Felix. Those were rumours!

11
00:00:30,712 --> 00:00:33,184
Yeah? Well how do you think rumours get started?

12
00:00:33,574 --> 00:00:36,323
It’s okay. I already flushed it down the toilet.

13
00:00:36,959 --> 00:00:38,607
I’ve only done it that one time.

14
00:00:38,669 --> 00:00:42,207
You don’t get to have me, not my body and sure as hell not my heart.

15
00:00:42,769 --> 00:00:43,707
We’re done.

16
00:00:44,996 --> 00:00:46,368
We should do this more often.

17
00:00:46,620 --> 00:00:47,465
Do what?

18
00:00:47,977 --> 00:00:49,170
Be friends.

19
00:01:39,182 --> 00:01:40,990
Nathanial Hawthorne once wrote:

20
00:01:41,342 --> 00:01:44,369
No man… for any considerable period…

21
00:01:45,255 --> 00:01:47,303
can wear one face to himself…

22
00:01:47,830 --> 00:01:49,477
and another to the multitude…

23
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:53,345
without finally getting bewildered as to which may be the true.

24
00:02:23,011 --> 00:02:23,912
Haley!

25
00:02:24,049 --> 00:02:26,933
Hey. I’m sorry to bother you so early…

26
00:02:28,728 --> 00:02:32,007
Nathan and I had a fight last night and he didn’t come home and...

27
00:02:32,108 --> 00:02:33,895
I talked to him. He’s okay.

28
00:02:33,976 --> 00:02:35,885
Oh well, do you know where he is?

29
00:02:36,644 --> 00:02:38,574
- No. 
- Okay, well…

30
00:02:38,663 --> 00:02:41,586
The next time you talk to him, can you… ask him to come home please?

31
00:02:41,939 --> 00:02:43,336
Okay, I will.

32
00:02:43,839 --> 00:02:47,392
Alright, well look, don’t worry yourself, okay Hales? I’m sure he’s fine. Alright?

33
00:02:47,653 --> 00:02:48,497
Okay. Bye.

34
00:02:51,832 --> 00:02:53,214
Thanks for covering for me man.

35
00:02:53,906 --> 00:02:55,190
You’re welcome but it sucked.

36
00:02:55,897 --> 00:02:56,987
I don’t wanna lie to Haley.

37
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,010
You just did.

38
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:03,096
Why don’t you go home? Work it out. It… didn’t sound like Haley was going to school anyway.

39
00:03:03,285 --> 00:03:05,471
Yeah, why would they have the Formal on a Sunday?

40
00:03:05,554 --> 00:03:08,125
I dunno; to keep the students from partying, getting wasted.

41
00:03:08,487 --> 00:03:10,161
Arguing with their wives.

42
00:03:11,088 --> 00:03:12,318
Yeah, well it didn’t work.

43
00:03:14,125 --> 00:03:15,594
How’d it go with Anna anyway?

44
00:03:16,174 --> 00:03:18,841
Well lets just say we didn’t exactly end the night together.

45
00:03:19,106 --> 00:03:20,218
Who’d you end up with?

46
00:03:24,596 --> 00:03:25,804
Only in Tree Hill.

47
00:03:26,531 --> 00:03:28,999
Ew, you two realise you’re related, right?

48
00:03:29,115 --> 00:03:29,827
Hi Brooke.

49
00:03:29,945 --> 00:03:31,819
Double ew if Tutor Wife is here.

50
00:03:31,948 --> 00:03:32,721
She’s not.

51
00:03:33,365 --> 00:03:34,089
What’s up?

52
00:03:34,293 --> 00:03:39,664
Um… my car is now out of commission, thanks to my jealous, spiteful stain of a neighbour…

53
00:03:39,954 --> 00:03:44,230
and I was sort of thinking… that… you might wanna walk to school together.

54
00:03:45,468 --> 00:03:48,051
Unless of course, you’re waiting for your ‘Boytoy’ here.

55
00:03:49,049 --> 00:03:51,547
Go ahead. I’ll catch up with you guys later.

56
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:52,417
Alright.

57
00:03:52,838 --> 00:03:53,728
Go home Nate.

58
00:03:54,302 --> 00:03:55,146
Work it out.

59
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:12,185
Well, well. Angel of the morning.

60
00:04:13,635 --> 00:04:16,562
Okay, look. I wasn’t with Lucas so just… chill out.

61
00:04:20,438 --> 00:04:21,571
Where were you Anna?

62
00:04:23,035 --> 00:04:24,309
I stayed at Peyton’s.

63
00:04:25,190 --> 00:04:27,801
Ah, that’s great. Mom and dad will love that!

64
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:28,949
Then don’t tell them.

65
00:04:29,184 --> 00:04:31,346
Just let me know when I need to start packing again.

66
00:04:44,774 --> 00:04:46,480
New digs for your return, hey Danny?

67
00:04:47,145 --> 00:04:49,628
No, new digs for your return.

68
00:04:50,566 --> 00:04:52,614
You did a hell of a job while I was away Keith.

69
00:04:57,103 --> 00:04:58,205
What do you say?

70
00:05:02,201 --> 00:05:04,257
- Who do you think did it? 
- Felix.

71
00:05:05,275 --> 00:05:08,132
We kind of… stopped benefiting.

72
00:05:10,831 --> 00:05:16,033
I’m glad! I mean, not about the… windshield thing but… about the rest of it.

73
00:05:16,191 --> 00:05:17,890
Why, because you don’t like him?

74
00:05:18,537 --> 00:05:19,177
No…

75
00:05:20,672 --> 00:05:21,976
because you’re better than that.

76
00:05:26,631 --> 00:05:27,941
I miss this, you know.

77
00:05:29,524 --> 00:05:30,655
Talking to you.

78
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:36,825
What happened to you?

79
00:05:38,510 --> 00:05:39,815
I’m not talking to you.

80
00:05:40,956 --> 00:05:41,674
Okay.

81
00:05:43,153 --> 00:05:45,315
Well if it makes you feel any better… Brooke dumped me.

82
00:05:47,024 --> 00:05:48,136
You told her didn’t you?

83
00:05:49,241 --> 00:05:50,701
About the dollhouse and TRIC.

84
00:05:51,828 --> 00:05:53,461
Thought she should know the truth.

85
00:05:55,218 --> 00:05:56,632
Whatever, I deserved it.

86
00:05:57,614 --> 00:06:01,249
It’s a rule of life Mouth; whatever crap you pull… always catches up to you.

87
00:06:01,587 --> 00:06:02,615
It’s a part of the game.

88
00:06:03,467 --> 00:06:05,217
It’s not a game, Felix.

89
00:06:05,974 --> 00:06:10,169
Come on Mouth. It took her less than and hour to crush me and hook up with Lucas.

90
00:06:10,388 --> 00:06:12,185
Lucas wouldn’t do that. He’s with Anna.

91
00:06:12,369 --> 00:06:13,147
Really?

92
00:06:18,509 --> 00:06:19,978
It’s okay to freak out, Mouth.

93
00:06:21,533 --> 00:06:22,927
I did last night.

94
00:06:35,865 --> 00:06:36,699
Hi.

95
00:06:39,577 --> 00:06:40,592
Sorry.

96
00:06:42,347 --> 00:06:43,186
I was…

97
00:06:44,416 --> 00:06:46,310
I was wrong last night and…

98
00:06:46,888 --> 00:06:50,014
I found your letter from the camp and I want you to go.


99
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:53,914
It’s not about the camp, Haley. It’s about trust.

100
00:06:57,475 --> 00:06:59,756
I want you to stop working with Chris.

101
00:07:00,467 --> 00:07:04,557
- He’s incredibly talented, Nathan. 
- I want you to stop seeing him.

102
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:12,556
I won’t do that.

103
00:07:26,456 --> 00:07:28,638
Hey. Wanna hear about my window?

104
00:07:29,554 --> 00:07:32,821
Somebody bashed in my car windshield last night. You believe that?

105
00:07:33,297 --> 00:07:35,033
I mean, could things get any worse?

106
00:07:38,117 --> 00:07:39,533
You wanna ask me that again?

107
00:07:46,228 --> 00:07:48,949
- What’s this? 
- An estimate for my windshield.

108
00:07:51,954 --> 00:07:54,381
- And you think I did it? 
- I know you did.

109
00:07:54,437 --> 00:07:57,084
I didn’t break you window baby… just your heart.

110
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:59,014
Please.

111
00:08:02,981 --> 00:08:05,840
With men like that in the world, it’s a wonder we’re not gay!

112
00:08:06,997 --> 00:08:08,451
See the way everybody’s looking at me?

113
00:08:09,536 --> 00:08:11,420
Nobody’s taking this seriously.

114
00:08:11,738 --> 00:08:14,708
Really? Because half the girls in P.E. wouldn’t change in front of me.

115
00:08:14,810 --> 00:08:16,812
It’s ‘cause you look better than they do, naked.

116
00:08:19,915 --> 00:08:21,369
Do you have any idea who did it?

117
00:08:23,780 --> 00:08:28,874
Well… if you ask me, they did you a favour; boys love lesbians.

118
00:08:30,621 --> 00:08:31,512
Come on.

119
00:08:33,196 --> 00:08:35,388
The old P. Sawyer woulda just rolled with this.

120
00:08:36,243 --> 00:08:38,649
Yeah, well I haven’t been the old P. Sawyer in a while, have I?

121
00:08:40,703 --> 00:08:42,264
Hey, your real friends are here for you.

122
00:08:57,092 --> 00:08:58,330
Unbelievable.

123
00:08:58,432 --> 00:09:01,930
Okay, you know what, I’m gonna get outta here. Do you wanna come with me?

124
00:09:03,231 --> 00:09:06,882
Yeah… but… I have a quiz next period and if I miss it –

125
00:09:06,959 --> 00:09:09,345
Nah it’s… it’s cool. I’ll see ya later.

126
00:09:09,815 --> 00:09:10,845
Okay.

127
00:09:35,202 --> 00:09:38,702
What’s up? Looking for your wife?

128
00:09:39,322 --> 00:09:42,742
You’re funny. You’re also done messing with Haley.

129
00:09:44,432 --> 00:09:48,539
- We’re just rehearsing, man. 
- No, you were rehearsing. That’s over now.

130
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:51,252
Why? Can’t you trust her?

131
00:09:52,531 --> 00:09:54,191
I mean, isn’t that what this is about?

132
00:09:54,729 --> 00:09:57,254
You love her… you married her…

133
00:09:57,965 --> 00:09:59,210
but can you trust her?

134
00:10:00,510 --> 00:10:04,221
Cos if you can, you got nothing to worry about right?

135
00:10:06,214 --> 00:10:07,919
Come on, man, I don’t have a problem with you.

136
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:17,480
You see, you do have a problem with me; a big problem.

137
00:10:17,545 --> 00:10:22,040
You could smile and act cool if you want to but the fact is, man: I used to destroy guys like you.

138
00:10:22,326 --> 00:10:23,212
Daily.

139
00:10:25,051 --> 00:10:28,208
It’d be a shame if something happened to this hand; you couldn’t play that little guitar anymore huh?

140
00:10:28,265 --> 00:10:31,512
Just like it’d be a shame if you were taking advantage of Haley.

141
00:10:37,909 --> 00:10:41,460
Don’t cry, rock star, ruin your make-up.

142
00:10:46,223 --> 00:10:47,274
Pick up.


143
00:10:49,323 --> 00:10:50,574
Pick up.

144
00:10:52,309 --> 00:10:53,953
You’ve reached Sawyer dredging.

145
00:10:54,035 --> 00:10:57,076
If you’d like to leave a message for Larry Sawyer, please do so after –

146
00:11:02,887 --> 00:11:03,767
Hey.

147
00:11:04,393 --> 00:11:05,218
Hey.

148
00:11:05,816 --> 00:11:09,196
So… I saw you cut out of lunch today.

149
00:11:11,479 --> 00:11:14,029
Just… wanted to know how you were doing.

150
00:11:15,805 --> 00:11:16,742
Been better.

151
00:11:21,401 --> 00:11:23,526
Hey. Come here.

152
00:11:29,796 --> 00:11:30,845
Sit down.

153
00:11:40,058 --> 00:11:42,491
So do you know who wrote it? On your locker.

154
00:11:44,267 --> 00:11:51,394
No. I don’t even wanna know. I just want it to all… go away. Just… all of it.

155
00:12:00,428 --> 00:12:01,338
You miss Jake, huh?

156
00:12:04,481 --> 00:12:05,531
You should go.

157
00:12:07,246 --> 00:12:09,596
- Peyton. 
- No– Okay.

158
00:12:09,704 --> 00:12:13,293
You can’t just walk in here and ask me something like that!

159
00:12:13,381 --> 00:12:16,637
When is the last time we even had a conversation about something real?

160
00:12:16,714 --> 00:12:18,310
I just thought you could use a friend.

161
00:12:18,388 --> 00:12:22,464
Yeah, I could use a friend, you know but you don’t qualify as that anymore, Lucas,

162
00:12:22,581 --> 00:12:25,996
because a real friend would know about all the crap I’ve been dealing with lately.

163
00:12:26,284 --> 00:12:27,066
Like what?

164
00:12:30,235 --> 00:12:31,730
Just go. Please.

165
00:12:34,078 --> 00:12:36,558
Okay. I’ll go.

166
00:12:42,287 --> 00:12:43,456
Whatever you think…

167
00:12:45,365 --> 00:12:47,526
I really do care about you, Peyton.

168
00:13:01,222 --> 00:13:03,239
You sneaking away without saying goodbye?

169
00:13:04,355 --> 00:13:06,117
Oh, actually I was…

170
00:13:07,653 --> 00:13:09,046
I was thinking about staying.

171
00:13:10,413 --> 00:13:12,789
Dan offered me a management position at the dealership.

172
00:13:13,787 --> 00:13:15,375
Did you say no to Charleston?

173
00:13:16,356 --> 00:13:19,050
Well, not yet but… I might.

174
00:13:21,386 --> 00:13:23,009
You know I care about you, Keith.

175
00:13:23,797 --> 00:13:24,446
Yeah.

176
00:13:25,229 --> 00:13:26,264
Then listen to me.

177
00:13:26,818 --> 00:13:29,565
I know how much teaching in Charleston means to you.

178
00:13:30,341 --> 00:13:32,824
I’ve seen you light up when you talk about it.

179
00:13:33,023 --> 00:13:35,107
Not as much as I light up when I talk about you.

180
00:13:37,441 --> 00:13:40,359
One of the reasons I fell for you was your independence.

181
00:13:41,789 --> 00:13:43,846
You made your own way in the world.

182
00:13:44,385 --> 00:13:48,199
You brother’s business is his. Charleston is yours.

183
00:13:49,381 --> 00:13:51,107
Don’t let him take that from you.

184
00:14:04,270 --> 00:14:06,923
- Can I give you a piece of advice? 
- Nice to see you too.

185
00:14:06,979 --> 00:14:10,347
Next time you wanna lie about something, you might wanna make sure your mom is in on it.

186
00:14:10,563 --> 00:14:12,627
She told me about Nathan sleeping here last night.

187
00:14:12,826 --> 00:14:16,891
Haley, Nathan just needed some time. If you were here, I’d have done the same thing.

188
00:14:17,127 --> 00:14:18,883
Lucas Eugene Scott!

189
00:14:19,289 --> 00:14:21,554
- Oo, that sounds bad. 
- Eugene?

190
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:27,720
- Why would you lie to me? 
- Yeah, get in line.

191
00:14:27,839 --> 00:14:31,888
- Mom, what are you talking about? 
- Dan’s heart condition. Is it genetic?

192
00:14:33,875 --> 00:14:36,087
- Yes. 
- Why didn’t you tell me?

193
00:14:36,175 --> 00:14:40,172
- What kind of doctor doesn’t call me?! 
- Mom, I told him you were in Florence.

194
00:14:40,249 --> 00:14:43,669
Why?! When there’s a fifty percent chance you have a genetic heart defect!

195
00:14:43,730 --> 00:14:47,448
- Nathan- 
- No, he’s… fine. He doesn’t have it. He took the test.

196
00:14:47,519 --> 00:14:48,457
But you didn’t?

197
00:14:49,767 --> 00:14:52,210
- Who told you? 
- You are taking that test.

198
00:14:52,276 --> 00:14:55,666
- No! I’m not. 
- Are you out of your mind?!

199
00:14:55,803 --> 00:15:00,499
How can you be so reckless and cavalier about a potentially fatal condition?

200
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:01,483
I’m gonna go home.

201
00:15:02,562 --> 00:15:04,626
You’re gonna give me the name of the doctor that you’ve spoken with

202
00:15:04,692 --> 00:15:07,211
and you’re packing a bag because I’m driving you to that test.

203
00:15:07,298 --> 00:15:09,966
No, I'm not taking the test. I don't wanna know!

204
00:15:10,043 --> 00:15:12,116
- Why not?!
- For lots of reasons.

205
00:15:12,372 --> 00:15:15,285
Basketball... the way I wanna live my life.

206
00:15:15,372 --> 00:15:19,274
Lucas, basketball is a game! Now I am glad that you have a talent

207
00:15:19,331 --> 00:15:22,118
but do you really think that I will put a game before your life?

208
00:15:22,300 --> 00:15:24,281
- I would. 
- Oh, grow up!

209
00:15:24,405 --> 00:15:28,531
That tragic hero crap only works in the movies and you know what they don't show you after they fade out?

210
00:15:28,613 --> 00:15:30,968
The hero’s mother putting her foot up his ass!

211
00:15:31,265 --> 00:15:34,690
Mom, you can threaten me all you want but you can’t make me take that test.

212
00:15:34,824 --> 00:15:37,737
I sure as hell can! You think about that!

213
00:15:38,622 --> 00:15:41,751
Until you come to your senses, your basketball days are over.

214
00:15:42,559 --> 00:15:43,205
Mom!

215
00:15:44,004 --> 00:15:47,071
You need parental permission to play and you just lost yours.

216
00:15:54,454 --> 00:15:56,638
Hey guys! Let’s jump.

217
00:15:58,190 --> 00:16:00,142
How bout a little two-on-two? Come on.

218
00:16:00,803 --> 00:16:03,081
Luke, I don’t know much man but I do know one thing;

219
00:16:03,685 --> 00:16:05,892
you damn sure aint touching no ball round here.

220
00:16:06,163 --> 00:16:08,489
- Alright, what’s going on? 
- Your mom told us bout your heart.

221
00:16:08,585 --> 00:16:12,353
- She said you’d be in danger if you played. 
- Yeah, we’d be in danger if we let you play.

222
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:13,515
She was scary Luke.

223
00:16:13,751 --> 00:16:14,954
Look guys, I’m fine.

224
00:16:15,170 --> 00:16:18,179
It might be true… but we’ll let your mom tell us that for sure.

225
00:16:19,485 --> 00:16:20,289
Let’s go.

226
00:16:41,743 --> 00:16:42,946
What going on with you?

227
00:16:43,786 --> 00:16:45,780
I heard about you heart test.

228
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:48,215
I’m fine.

229
00:16:48,957 --> 00:16:50,007
Are you sure?

230
00:16:53,364 --> 00:16:55,064
I’m not gonna see Chris anymore.

231
00:16:56,657 --> 00:17:00,364
I don’t want it to come between us. I just-I don’t want anything to come between us.

232
00:17:08,081 --> 00:17:08,812
Lucas.

233
00:17:09,391 --> 00:17:10,998
You told my mom about the heart test.

234
00:17:13,445 --> 00:17:16,445
Well I’m glad she knows. If it forces you to reconsider.

235
00:17:17,066 --> 00:17:18,448
You promised me.

236
00:17:20,736 --> 00:17:21,438
Lucas!

237
00:17:23,870 --> 00:17:25,381
What did you see when you died?

238
00:17:27,039 --> 00:17:31,438
After the accident; when your heart stopped. What’d you see?

239
00:17:33,384 --> 00:17:35,385
Because when my heart failed, I saw you.

240
00:17:36,931 --> 00:17:39,051
Your mother can’t bear to lose you, Lucas.

241
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:41,299
Neither can I.

242
00:17:52,926 --> 00:17:54,232
I… I rang the doorbell.

243
00:17:56,721 --> 00:17:57,437
I know.

244
00:17:58,399 --> 00:17:59,527
I just didn’t wanna answer.

245
00:18:02,592 --> 00:18:04,816
I’m sorry I blew you off at lunch today.

246
00:18:05,343 --> 00:18:10,043
You know, it’s really starting to be a pattern; you showing up in my room to apologise to me.

247
00:18:12,218 --> 00:18:14,282
You’re right. But…

248
00:18:19,234 --> 00:18:23,990
At my last school… there were some rumours about me.

249
00:18:24,865 --> 00:18:28,951
About a relationship I was having... with another girl.

250
00:18:32,505 --> 00:18:36,330
I tried to ignore it but the stories just… kept getting worse.

251
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:39,960
Until, finally, my parents decided to move us here.

252
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:43,713
And that’s why Felix is so protective of me.

253
00:18:44,746 --> 00:18:46,734
He was really happy in our last town.

254
00:18:47,511 --> 00:18:50,784
Okay, but I thought you said they were just… rumours.

255
00:18:51,311 --> 00:18:52,453
It doesn’t matter.

256
00:18:53,313 --> 00:18:54,843
You know how high school is.

257
00:18:56,103 --> 00:19:00,246
Once a story gets out, it… might as well be true.

258
00:19:02,944 --> 00:19:06,743
So when I saw your locker, and the way that people were looking at you,

259
00:19:08,135 --> 00:19:10,511
I guess… it scared me.

260
00:19:13,082 --> 00:19:15,897
It was… a horrible time for me, Peyton.

261
00:19:21,331 --> 00:19:22,481
What are you gonna do?

262
00:19:23,121 --> 00:19:24,007
I don’t know.

263
00:19:24,559 --> 00:19:29,733
You could always just… let it go. I mean, you’re not gay. Right?

264
00:19:32,005 --> 00:19:32,777
Come here.

265
00:19:40,003 --> 00:19:40,729
Read that.

266
00:19:43,239 --> 00:19:47,585
First they put away the dealers… then they put away the prostitutes…

267
00:19:48,015 --> 00:19:52,802
then they shoot away the bums… and… beat and bash the queers…

268
00:19:54,605 --> 00:19:58,337
Turned away asylum seekers, fed us suspicions and fears,

269
00:19:58,634 --> 00:20:01,154
we didn’t raise our voice, we didn’t make a fuss…

270
00:20:01,557 --> 00:20:04,957
- it’s funny, there was no one left to notice- 
- when they came for us.

271
00:20:06,883 --> 00:20:09,592
Anna, it’s not about who I am, okay?

272
00:20:09,678 --> 00:20:13,402
It’s about who they are, they are people who hate and they divide

273
00:20:13,468 --> 00:20:16,164
and the feed off of people that don’t fight back.

274
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:22,939
Yeah, I… I could laugh this off. But… what about the girl that can’t?

275
00:20:23,723 --> 00:20:24,849
Who’s gonna help her?

276
00:20:27,118 --> 00:20:29,426
Silence only makes them stronger.

277
00:21:11,201 --> 00:21:12,230
Hey, Haley.

278
00:21:13,204 --> 00:21:14,289
You here to see Chris?

279
00:21:21,615 --> 00:21:22,839
Oh, sorry. Um…

280
00:21:24,483 --> 00:21:28,257
You know what, I’ll… I’ll catch him later. It’s okay.

281
00:21:47,671 --> 00:21:48,403
Keith?

282
00:21:49,305 --> 00:21:50,015
Hey.

283
00:21:51,470 --> 00:21:55,735
I… I accepted Dan’s offer.

284
00:21:58,295 --> 00:22:04,578
You know, Charleston was always about… hope for me, Jules;

285
00:22:05,355 --> 00:22:07,986
a place where maybe I could… find something special.

286
00:22:09,052 --> 00:22:10,415
But I found that right here.

287
00:22:13,328 --> 00:22:14,156
With you.

288
00:22:17,460 --> 00:22:18,914
You’ve given me that hope.

289
00:22:25,837 --> 00:22:27,331
You are the best.

290
00:22:28,013 --> 00:22:29,007
What do I owe you?

291
00:22:29,968 --> 00:22:30,685
Nothing.

292
00:22:31,448 --> 00:22:32,820
I called in a couple of favours.

293
00:22:33,357 --> 00:22:35,048
Are you serious? Thank you.

294
00:22:35,138 --> 00:22:37,704
- Hi Brooke! 
- Hi.

295
00:22:38,447 --> 00:22:39,025
Hey.

296
00:22:40,093 --> 00:22:40,910
You ready?

297
00:22:41,478 --> 00:22:42,149
Yeah.

298
00:22:42,349 --> 00:22:43,501
Okay. Bye.

299
00:22:45,062 --> 00:22:46,946
Um… so…

300
00:22:47,356 --> 00:22:50,028
I guess I’ll… see you at school.

301
00:22:50,905 --> 00:22:51,892
Yeah.

302
00:23:32,079 --> 00:23:34,031
Hey, Luke! Can I talk to you?

303
00:23:41,085 --> 00:23:43,057
