304
00:23:43,138 --> 00:23:44,481
Yeah, you know, she needed some help.

305
00:23:44,659 --> 00:23:47,163
Well I wanna pay for it. I took some money out of the bank.

306
00:23:47,517 --> 00:23:50,850
- Mouth, you don’t have to do that, alright? 
- Please! I want to.

307
00:23:51,337 --> 00:23:53,287
- Mouth...
- I’m the one who did it.

308
00:23:55,504 --> 00:23:57,101
I broke her windshield.

309
00:24:03,071 --> 00:24:08,729
Miss Sawyer, you know we have a policy regarding wardrobe that’s offensive or profane.

310
00:24:09,205 --> 00:24:12,989
Does that policy extend to lockers, cos you haven’t removed that yet have you?

311
00:24:13,485 --> 00:24:17,279
You know the drill; go to the office and change or be sent home.

312
00:24:18,447 --> 00:24:21,491
Okay, Mr Turner, have you ever heard of Victor Hara?

313
00:24:22,656 --> 00:24:27,044
No? Um… he was this musician, right, and he fought in justice with his songs

314
00:24:27,105 --> 00:24:30,684
and when they broke his hands and when they taunted him, he just sang even louder.

315
00:24:30,805 --> 00:24:35,184
Look, Peyton, oppression’s not exactly a mystery to me, okay?

316
00:24:36,275 --> 00:24:38,896
- I feel your pain. 
- No… no you don’t.

317
00:24:38,994 --> 00:24:42,619
Okay, I’m sorry, but you don’t know anything about my pain.

318
00:24:42,767 --> 00:24:47,017
Maybe so but there are counsellors you can talk to. Literature you can read.

319
00:24:47,093 --> 00:24:49,664
Okay, I’m not gay! Mr Turner.

320
00:24:49,834 --> 00:24:53,827
But you know what; if I was I wouldn’t let other people tear me down because of it

321
00:24:53,919 --> 00:24:57,769
and I sure as hell wouldn't be looking for my answers in-in one of your pamphlets!

322
00:24:58,584 --> 00:25:02,864
Policy is clear Peyton. Remove the shirt or be suspended.

323
00:25:06,274 --> 00:25:07,010
Fine.

324
00:25:09,509 --> 00:25:11,788
Can you hear my song now, Mr Turner?

325
00:25:15,408 --> 00:25:17,425
Enjoy your suspension Miss Sawyer.

326
00:25:27,046 --> 00:25:28,627
You probably think I’m an idiot.

327
00:25:29,323 --> 00:25:31,755
Actually, I’m kinda hoping you have an evil twin.

328
00:25:31,950 --> 00:25:33,697
Look, vandalising Brooke’s car…

329
00:25:34,285 --> 00:25:35,631
Mouth, that’s just not you.

330
00:25:36,149 --> 00:25:37,624
I guess that’s why I did it.

331
00:25:39,220 --> 00:25:41,186
Girls see me as their little brother.

332
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:43,204
They always tell me how nice I am.

333
00:25:43,311 --> 00:25:44,679
Well that’s cos you are nice!

334
00:25:45,580 --> 00:25:47,146
That’s why you have so many friends, Mouth.

335
00:25:47,214 --> 00:25:48,407
And no girlfriend.

336
00:25:49,272 --> 00:25:51,508
Haley fell for Nathan when he was a jerk.

337
00:25:51,734 --> 00:25:53,172
Brooke went for Felix.

338
00:25:53,292 --> 00:25:56,649
Luke, you’ve screwed up a lot this year and you’ve had a different girl every week.

339
00:25:58,396 --> 00:26:00,909
Sorry. I just…

340
00:26:01,462 --> 00:26:03,234
I try to be honest with Brooke.

341
00:26:03,925 --> 00:26:07,095
I told her the truth and then she left with Felix anyway.

342
00:26:07,176 --> 00:26:08,924
Yeah, to end things with him.

343
00:26:09,152 --> 00:26:10,816
But I didn’t know that at the time.

344
00:26:11,999 --> 00:26:16,904
All I knew was that I was at another party where… everybody had someone, but me.

345
00:26:19,111 --> 00:26:21,937
Then I… kinda got drunk.

346
00:26:22,168 --> 00:26:23,263
You were drinking?

347
00:26:23,611 --> 00:26:24,580
Sort of.

348
00:26:25,501 --> 00:26:27,268
I had… one drink.

349
00:26:28,036 --> 00:26:29,381
But it was a big one.

350
00:26:29,822 --> 00:26:31,716
Next thing I knew, I was at Brooke’s house.

351
00:26:31,830 --> 00:26:33,919
Wait, you drove to Brooke’s house… wasted?

352
00:26:34,020 --> 00:26:35,183
I rode my bike.

353
00:26:36,038 --> 00:26:37,774
I… fell a couple of times.

354
00:26:39,804 --> 00:26:44,864
In the morning, I felt terrible about what I did and even worse when I found out you fixed it.

355
00:26:46,867 --> 00:26:48,578
You know she thinks Felix did it.

356
00:26:49,186 --> 00:26:52,269
I know… and I’m gonna tell her the truth.

357
00:26:55,417 --> 00:26:58,095
You know, I like Brooke a lot.

358
00:26:59,466 --> 00:27:01,402
I guess I have for a long time.

359
00:27:03,265 --> 00:27:05,463
But it was okay when you guys were together.

360
00:27:07,182 --> 00:27:09,677
I guess I always thought your hearts were the same.

361
00:27:29,333 --> 00:27:32,854
Hey! Hang on a second!

362
00:27:34,094 --> 00:27:35,205
What is this!?

363
00:27:36,981 --> 00:27:39,779
- That should cover your window. 
- Then you did do it.

364
00:27:39,849 --> 00:27:41,412
No. I didn’t.

365
00:27:47,007 --> 00:27:49,613
- Who’s the ho? 
- She not a ho.

366
00:27:49,772 --> 00:27:51,877
Her name’s Kayla and she was my last girlfriend.

367
00:27:53,463 --> 00:27:56,484
We dated for two years. I was never happier.

368
00:27:58,477 --> 00:28:02,014
Then, one day… she passed me a note… and that was it.

369
00:28:02,382 --> 00:28:05,546
I don’t believe you. Cos you said you only do ‘Friends with Benefits’.

370
00:28:05,726 --> 00:28:06,986
I have, since then.

371
00:28:07,963 --> 00:28:09,331
See, I was just like you Brooke.

372
00:28:10,513 --> 00:28:14,068
Doing ‘Friends with Benefits’ because I was afraid of getting my heart broken again.

373
00:28:16,419 --> 00:28:17,856
But I guess it doesn’t matter.

374
00:28:24,225 --> 00:28:27,974
So what, I’m supposed to believe you didn’t break my windshield but you’re paying for it anyway?

375
00:28:29,197 --> 00:28:32,182
You don’t have to believe it. Any of it.

376
00:28:34,445 --> 00:28:35,509
But it’s true.

377
00:28:49,926 --> 00:28:50,854
What’s with them?

378
00:28:51,039 --> 00:28:54,459
Oh, huh, Dan told my mom about the HCM test.

379
00:28:54,906 --> 00:28:57,296
I guess that’s my bad for trusting him to keep a secret right?

380
00:28:58,320 --> 00:28:59,588
He didn’t tell her.

381
00:29:01,827 --> 00:29:02,686
I did.

382
00:29:04,222 --> 00:29:04,976
I told her.

383
00:29:05,799 --> 00:29:06,737
Why?

384
00:29:07,147 --> 00:29:10,198
Because I knew that if she found out, she’d make you take the test.

385
00:29:10,295 --> 00:29:13,254
She’s not gonna make me take the test and that sucks that you told her!

386
00:29:13,766 --> 00:29:15,411
After I covered for you with Haley!

387
00:29:15,513 --> 00:29:18,063
About where I crashed for a night, not about my life.

388
00:29:18,171 --> 00:29:20,419
You know what, whatever. You promised me.

389
00:29:20,971 --> 00:29:23,035
Guess Dan’s not the only one I can’t trust.

390
00:29:24,601 --> 00:29:26,096
Hey, yo, Luke. He’s right, man.

391
00:29:26,824 --> 00:29:28,927
I mean you’re wrong not to take that test, dawg.

392
00:29:29,870 --> 00:29:32,102
Come on man, it’s not fair to us or your mom.

393
00:29:32,879 --> 00:29:33,792
Unbelievable.

394
00:29:34,867 --> 00:29:38,548
You know what, Skills, why don’t you just run with Nathan from now on.

395
00:29:39,136 --> 00:29:41,452
How bout you take the test and we all run together?

396
00:29:57,425 --> 00:29:59,033
- Hey. 
- Hey!

397
00:29:59,284 --> 00:30:02,193
Um… I was gonna call you… in a while.

398
00:30:02,367 --> 00:30:06,313
Um… I’m sorry to just drop by. I just need somebody to talk to.

399
00:30:06,395 --> 00:30:07,097
Stop!

400
00:30:08,004 --> 00:30:09,980
I just-I need you, Brooke.

401
00:30:11,593 --> 00:30:17,861
I just… there’s so much stuff piling up and I don’t think I can handle it anymore.

402
00:30:17,932 --> 00:30:19,862
Okay. Well what’s going on? Talk to me,

403
00:30:19,979 --> 00:30:22,647
I mean… you said you’re not feeling like yourself but what’s wrong?

404
00:30:22,759 --> 00:30:23,794
Just everything!

405
00:30:24,490 --> 00:30:28,669
You know, like Karen is really counting on me at the club and I don’t even have a band!

406
00:30:28,848 --> 00:30:32,708
You know, and I’m suspended and that’s gonna look great on my transcripts and...

407
00:30:35,567 --> 00:30:40,864
and I miss Jake and… Jenny… and my mom.

408
00:30:40,966 --> 00:30:43,475
Hey. It’s gonna be okay.

409
00:30:43,583 --> 00:30:47,556
I should be stronger than this, you know, I should and I don’t wanna be a person that…

410
00:30:47,623 --> 00:30:51,846
that needs help but I… I feel all alone.

411
00:30:52,722 --> 00:30:54,576
You are not alone.

412
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:58,241
Okay, you have me no matter what.

413
00:30:59,423 --> 00:31:00,602
Come here.

414
00:31:01,676 --> 00:31:05,793
Oh, I’m just glad you’re not seeing Felix anymore, I missed you.

415
00:31:06,535 --> 00:31:09,481
Um… yeah, I...

416
00:31:11,993 --> 00:31:13,785
Oh. Hey.

417
00:31:15,353 --> 00:31:17,088
- Oh god, um… 
- No, no.

418
00:31:17,155 --> 00:31:20,079
- No, I’m sorry to interrupt. 
- No, Peyton. Don’t go.

419
00:31:20,185 --> 00:31:22,849
- It’s cool, I’ll call you later. 
- No! Peyton!

420
00:31:29,041 --> 00:31:30,244
I’ll let you know


421
00:31:31,441 --> 00:31:34,144
When it comes

422
00:31:34,752 --> 00:31:37,262
When it comes

423
00:31:37,931 --> 00:31:40,173
I’ll let you know

424
00:31:40,845 --> 00:31:44,414
But don’t stay up for me, no

425
00:31:45,115 --> 00:31:47,056
Don’t wait up for me

426
00:31:48,015 --> 00:31:50,056
- Hey.
- Hey.

427
00:31:50,257 --> 00:31:51,177
Sounds good.

428
00:31:51,875 --> 00:31:54,244
Thanks. It’s getting there, you know.

429
00:31:55,208 --> 00:31:57,312
Uh, listen. I…

430
00:31:58,227 --> 00:32:00,993
I hope you know how much I appreciate everything that you’ve done for me.

431
00:32:04,043 --> 00:32:08,017
Um… but I don’t… really think we should work together… anymore.

432
00:32:08,857 --> 00:32:10,890
So it got to you? Nathan.

433
00:32:11,243 --> 00:32:14,489
No, I just, I think it’s for the best. You know?

434
00:32:16,358 --> 00:32:18,769
Well… it’s just as well.

435
00:32:19,420 --> 00:32:25,360
You know those… labels from New York? They offered me a… showcase.

436
00:32:25,698 --> 00:32:27,018
I think I’m gonna take it.

437
00:32:27,504 --> 00:32:29,302
Wow, that’s great Chris.

438
00:32:29,410 --> 00:32:34,370
Yeah. I’m leaving tonight, so I won’t be able to… play the show at TRIC anyway.

439
00:32:35,787 --> 00:32:38,600
So… I guess this is goodbye.

440
00:32:45,182 --> 00:32:46,090
Thanks.

441
00:32:49,426 --> 00:32:50,827
Wait, Haley, come here.

442
00:33:00,493 --> 00:33:01,763
What are you doing?

443
00:33:02,828 --> 00:33:03,755
Haley.

444
00:33:04,358 --> 00:33:07,015
Is that what this was all about; you just hitting on me?

445
00:33:07,206 --> 00:33:09,202
- Haley, it’s okay. 
- No, it’s not okay.

446
00:33:09,305 --> 00:33:11,558
I can’t believe- you just did that.

447
00:33:12,351 --> 00:33:13,758
Come with me to New York.

448
00:33:14,154 --> 00:33:18,275
What!? In case you missed something: I’m married.

449
00:33:18,382 --> 00:33:21,429
So you made a mistake. Are you gonna let that keep you from the rest of your life, Haley?

450
00:33:21,490 --> 00:33:24,418
- I did not make a mistake! 
- Haley, you owe it to your music.

451
00:33:24,486 --> 00:33:28,254
You owe it to yourself. Your dreams are a bus ride away.

452
00:33:28,766 --> 00:33:30,439
I know you want this Haley.

453
00:33:33,613 --> 00:33:37,047
No, you’re wrong, I don’t. I don’t want it; I don’t want any of it.

454
00:33:38,048 --> 00:33:39,688
It was always there between us, Haley.

455
00:33:41,715 --> 00:33:43,281
Whether you admit it or not.

456
00:34:01,904 --> 00:34:03,546
You cancelling your club night?

457
00:34:03,956 --> 00:34:04,699
Yeah.

458
00:34:06,118 --> 00:34:07,294
Because of the rumours?

459
00:34:07,822 --> 00:34:09,573
Because I can’t sing and dance.

460
00:34:11,659 --> 00:34:13,987
You know what, I’d really rather be alone right now.

461
00:34:16,357 --> 00:34:17,161
Okay.

462
00:34:18,016 --> 00:34:22,634
But… I just wanted to tell you how inspired I was when I saw you at school today.

463
00:34:22,716 --> 00:34:25,342
You know what, Anna, that’s great! You were inspired,

464
00:34:25,419 --> 00:34:29,919
but when I needed you to stand by me, you blew me off! So I don’t need you here now!

465
00:34:50,208 --> 00:34:52,603
Hey, Rick, it’s uh… Peyton.

466
00:35:00,359 --> 00:35:01,742
Hey man, come on in.

467
00:35:02,555 --> 00:35:03,775
Is this my apology?

468
00:35:04,051 --> 00:35:06,641
No, this is Haley’s apology. I don’t owe you one.

469
00:35:06,927 --> 00:35:10,598
You know why? Because nobody wants to lose you, Luke;

470
00:35:10,845 --> 00:35:14,506
not your mom, not Keith… not Haley, not me.

471
00:35:15,971 --> 00:35:17,782
There’s nothing wrong with my heart, Nate.

472
00:35:17,952 --> 00:35:20,562
Yeah? That’s what you said after you car accident.

473
00:35:21,171 --> 00:35:23,460
You told me you didn’t wanna be afraid to live your life.

474
00:35:23,610 --> 00:35:25,504
- That’s right. 
- Well I don’t buy it, Luke.

475
00:35:25,586 --> 00:35:27,701
I think there’s something in your heart you’re running from.

476
00:35:28,222 --> 00:35:29,364
Okay, what are you: psychic?

477
00:35:29,681 --> 00:35:31,418
You can make jokes about it all you want

478
00:35:32,365 --> 00:35:34,279
but you know there’s a girl you had feelings for.

479
00:35:35,272 --> 00:35:38,068
- Nathan- 
- Look me in the eye. Tell me I’m wrong.

480
00:35:40,562 --> 00:35:41,325
See?

481
00:35:42,410 --> 00:35:45,703
Now you can be mad at me all you want; you can say your heart’s fine…

482
00:35:46,208 --> 00:35:50,735
but till you tell this girl how you feel… your heart’s gonna be flawed.

483
00:35:53,147 --> 00:35:54,325
You need to talk to her Luke.

484
00:36:16,749 --> 00:36:20,585
Peyton, it’s me. Will you call me back; I’m worried about you, okay?

485
00:36:23,080 --> 00:36:24,165
She’ll be okay.

486
00:36:25,302 --> 00:36:26,351
You can go.

487
00:36:27,267 --> 00:36:28,281
Do I have to?

488
00:36:28,665 --> 00:36:29,812
- Felix! 
- Brooke.

